## Setting Groups & Keys

### General (existing)
`site_name`, `site_tagline`, `business_phone`, `business_email`, `business_address`, `business_hours`

### Branding (existing)
`logo`, `logo_dark`, `favicon`, `primary_color`

### Contact (new)
`business_whatsapp`, `business_viber`, `business_maps_url`, `business_landmark`, `delivery_threshold`, `delivery_time`

### Hero (new ‚Äî JSON type)
`hero_slide_1`, `hero_slide_2`, `hero_slide_3`
Each stores: `{ image, eyebrow, title, subtitle, cta_text, cta_url, cta2_text, cta2_url }`
Title supports HTML (`<br>`, `<em>`), rendered with `{!! !!}` in Blade.

### Homepage (new ‚Äî mixed)
- `trust_items` ‚Äî JSON array of 4 `{ icon, heading, subtext }`
- `proof_stat`, `proof_label` ‚Äî plain text
- `proof_details` ‚Äî JSON array of 3 `{ value, label }`
- `homepage_categories` ‚Äî JSON array of 4 `{ icon, label, name, hook, image_url, link }`
- `cta_band_headline`, `cta_band_subtext` ‚Äî plain text (headline supports HTML)

### SEO / Social / Footer (existing)
`meta_title`, `meta_description`, `og_image`, social URLs, footer text

## Image Upload Keys

Allowed in `SiteSettingsController::upload()`:
- **Brand:** `logo`, `logo_dark`, `favicon`, `og_image` ‚Üí auto-saved directly to setting
- **Hero slides:** `hero_1_image`, `hero_2_image`, `hero_3_image` ‚Üí returns URL only (admin embeds into JSON)
- **Categories:** `cat_1_image` ‚Ä¶ `cat_4_image` ‚Üí returns URL only (admin embeds into JSON)

## Admin UI Custom Editors

Detected by `item.key` in `WebsiteSettings` render loop:

| Key pattern | Editor component | Fields |
|-------------|-----------------|--------|
| `hero_slide_1/2/3` | `HeroSlideEditor` | image upload + eyebrow, title, subtitle, 2√óCTA |
| `trust_items` | `TrustItemsEditor` | 4 rows: icon, heading, subtext |
| `proof_details` | `ProofDetailsEditor` | 3 rows: value, label |
| `homepage_categories` | `CategoriesEditor` | 4 rows: icon, label, name, hook, image upload, link |
| `*hours*` (json) | `BusinessHoursEditor` | 7 day rows with open/closed text |
| everything else | Auto-rendered | image/color/boolean/textarea/text input |

## How to Add a New Editable Setting

1. **Migration** ‚Äî Add row to `site_settings` via `DB::table('site_settings')->updateOrInsert(...)` with `key`, `value`, `type` (`text`/`json`/`image`/`boolean`/`color`), `group`, `label`, `description`, `is_public`
2. **Blade** ‚Äî Replace hardcoded value with `\App\Models\SiteSetting::get('your_key', 'fallback')`
3. **Admin UI** ‚Äî Plain text/boolean/color fields appear automatically in the matching tab. Only add a custom editor component in `SettingsPage.tsx` if the field is a JSON array that needs visual editing.

## Blade Pattern (always use this)

```php
@php
    $value = \App\Models\SiteSetting::get('key', 'default');
@endphp
{{ $value }}          {{-- text ‚Äî auto-escaped --}}
{!! $value !!}        {{-- HTML ‚Äî only for admin-controlled content --}}
```

## Common Gotchas

- `SiteSetting::get()` reads from cache. Cache is busted automatically on every save via `SiteSetting::bust()` inside `update()` and `upload()` (direct keys only).
- Hero/category images are NOT auto-saved to the setting on upload ‚Äî the API returns the URL and the admin UI embeds it into the JSON before saving with PUT.
- The `layout.blade.php` `@php` block must come BEFORE `@verbatim` (which wraps the CSS) ‚Äî Blade expressions inside `@verbatim` are not processed.
- JSON settings with `{!! !!}` in Blade are safe because only the owner can edit them (authenticated API, owner role required).
